First Read: 17-Mar-26
HB631 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 Relating to Etowah County; to repeal Sections
4 45-28-120, 45-28-140, 45-28-160, and 45-28-220, Code of
5 Alabama 1975, as obsolete.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
7 Section 1. (a) Section 45-28-120, Code of Alabama 1975,
8 requiring Etowah County to pay health insurance premiums of
9 laid-off employees, is repealed.
10 (b) Section 45-28-140, Code of Alabama 1975,
11 authorizing the county commission, by resolution, to allow
12 certain charitable and volunteer organizations to have
13 equipment repaired and to purchase gasoline or motor fuel from
14 the county at cost, is repealed.
15 (c) Section 45-28-160, Code of Alabama 1975,
16 authorizing any county officer or person designated to draw
17 warrants or checks on the county treasury to use mechanical or
18 facsimile devices for signatures on warrants or checks, is
19 repealed.
20 (d) Section 45-28-220, Code of Alabama 1975, requiring
21 every applicant for a license to hold a public concert or
22 other event to have written prior approval from the Etowah
23 County Commission two weeks before the date of the event, is
24 repealed.
25 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
26 1, 2026.
